---
name: IsaacLab task authoring
description: Decompose Isaac Lab feature work into reviewable tasks with validation steps.
---

Use this skill when a request is broad and needs to be broken into concrete implementation steps for an Isaac Lab repository.

## Playbook
- Identify the relevant task config, environment logic, asset definitions, wrappers, scripts, docs, and tests.
- Split config changes from simulator or runtime changes whenever possible.
- For each subtask, record the likely files, the main technical risk, and the smallest useful validation command or smoke check.
- Highlight when the work likely touches observations, actions, rewards, terminations, resets, training config, or documentation together.

## Output
- Produce a concise, execution-ready task list.
- Make validation expectations explicit.
